{
  "stem": "1641.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I just had enough time to go to some of my friends and told them that, if by some miracle you survive it, would you tell my parents when you get home or, you know, my family, if you get home, that I-- I perished here in September '44 with medical-- probably I get malaria or some other horrible diseases injected into my body and so forth.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was sure I'm going to die.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyhow, next day we went over to the other block-- we went-- we went-- that was opposite the other one.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was-- I think it was number 28 we went to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the end of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From there was just a wide fence to be seen, all that was on the corner of the Auschwitz camp past-- we could only see out through the wires and then the outside perimeter of the camp.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was hidden away from the other buildings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there he put us in this room, all the 24 of us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we got better food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He ordered special, good food to be brought in because he wanted the experiments to be carried out under, you know, normal, healthy-- on healthy people, what-- what diseases he can-- what the [INAUDIBLE] can cause to healthy people.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had double amount of bread, and the-- the soup actually had potato pieces in it, which was fantastic.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we-- we didn't suffer so much from it, and we didn't have to do anything, just lie on the beds.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And every day, he would call out one or two.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Schumacher, ?] SS captain.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he had a Jewish helper, a doctor who had to assist him and do what operations he had to [INAUDIBLE] on.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
